<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE - INPUT
        SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The input shaft can be removed without disassembling the transmission.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and washers that fasten the input bearing retainer to the main case. Remove
                the input bearing retainer.
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303333">(Figure 33)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303333" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303333.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 33. Remove Input Bearing Retainer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a scraper to remove the sealant material between the input bearing retainer and main
                case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>A black shipping seal may be on the input shaft. Remove and discard the seal.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the inner snap ring that holds the bearing on the input shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303334">(Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303334" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303334.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 34. Remove Inner Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing from the shaft with a suitable tool.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>If the snap ring is not out far enough for the tool to grip, pull the input shaft out until the tool can
            be installed on the snap ring
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303335">(Figure 35</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303335" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303335.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Pull Input Shaft Out to Access Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spacer from the input shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303336">(Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303336" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303336.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 36. Remove Spacer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the gear that holds the input shaft in the gear
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303337">(Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303337" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303337.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 37. Remove Snap Ring From Gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303338">(Figure 38)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303338" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303338.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 38. Remove Input Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
